Individual Satisfaction per Year (2 pt)

Copy and run the following code to define the sample_n_groups() function.

sample_n_groups = function(grouped_df, size, replace = FALSE, weight=NULL) {
  grp_var <- grouped_df %>% 
    groups %>%
    unlist %>% 
    as.character
  random_grp <- grouped_df %>% 
    summarise() %>% 
    sample_n(size, replace, weight) %>% 
    mutate(unique_id = 1:NROW(.))
  grouped_df %>% 
    right_join(random_grp, by=grp_var) %>% 
    group_by_(grp_var) 
}

Set 2 as a seed using set.seed() command. Start with soep data and group_by() person. From personal observations sample 5 (pseudo-)random people using the new sample_n_groups() function. T-hrowback on t-Tests (2 pt)

Remember the two kinds of t-Tests:

  • unpaired two sample t-Test
  • paired two sample t-Test (= repeated t-Test or panel t-Test)
before_after <- soep %>%
  filter(complete.cases(.)) %>% # use complete cases
  filter(year == 2000 | year == 2004) %>% # only use year 2000 or 2004
  group_by(id) %>% # look at id groups
  filter(n() == 2)  # only keep groups with exactly two observations/rows

For before_after data,

  • Please run a t.test() on variables with paired=TRUE that works and make sense (0.5 pt).
  • Please run a t.test() on variables with paired=TRUE that works and does not make sense (0.5 pt).
  • Please run a t.test() on variables with paired=FALSE that works and does not make sense (0.5 pt).
  • Please write down a t.test() on variables with paired=FALSE that does not work (0.5 pt). Put the non-working command in comments (otherwise the document cannot be knitted).
